<Author>NTLibran
<Content>Bearable but glad to leave The hotel lobby has been updated to have more of a modern feel but past that the property is in need of a makeover. Rooms are quite small and a little on the musty side, the shower pressure is very poor and soundproofing is non-existent. We were kept awake all night due to our 鈥榥eighbours鈥?snoring and the next guests that moved in knew we were from Australia because they could hear us on a telephone call. There are no fridges in the rooms which makes it hard to keep any food. There is also no air-conditioning, which wasn鈥檛 a problem for us as we were there in winter but I would imaging the rooms would get hot during summer.There is a Metro station about 3 blocks away from the hotel but as first timers to Mexico City we didn鈥檛 find the location was all that suitable to tourists, the hotel is situated on a street of electrical shops 鈥?if you need a remote control, a TV or a memory card you are set, however, if you are after food, a laundry or anything else you will have to venture further. We arrived late afternoon and didn鈥檛 feel safe to go exploring in the dark so we had dinner in the hotel, the food is below average and slow to arrive but the restaurant staff are real characters. Once we were more familiar with the area we explored a little further and found some decent restaurants and shops, having said that ,we tried to be off the streets and back in the hotel by 9pm. I believe Zona Rosa is a better option if you want to feel more at ease.Some reception staff were helpful, others didn鈥檛 want to know you or tell you anything. For example, we learn鈥檛 on our last day that if you put down a refundable deposit they gave you a remote control to enable the cable service on the television 鈥?which means you receive English speaking channels. They have 3 computers with very reasonably priced internet access available for guests, there was a number of times we wanted to use them and they weren鈥檛 working, but the problems were normally rectified in under an hour.This hotel is reasonably priced and comfortable enough for a one night stay, for a longer period I would recommend looking elsewhere. 
