<Author>patanete
<Content>good hotel and good deal I come to this hotel almost every year from 2004 after reading the first review in TripAdvisor.Here is mine.I like very much this city and think this hotel is ideal to enjoy it.All sights in the Centro Historico are a pleasant walk away,the El Salvador street are vey busy by day but a little intimidating by night,like all the old part of the city,not very well lighted,but I never felt unsafe,and I go out and return to the hotel late and sometimes very late.The Salto de Agua metro station are four blocks away and this line takes you to the zona rosa directly and also to Tapo bus station.There is also nearer the San Juan de Letran metro st. but that line is not very useful and you must to transfer in Salto de Agua to go to other parts of the city.Taxi is easy because the hotel is 50 meters of the Eje Central a very busy avenue.If you prefer,the hotel calls you a safer taxi.Inside the hotel,is all quietness,is a modern buiding,well maintained ,with five floors and a lift.The rooms are very clean,carpeted,cable TV,good mattresses and big windows open to several courts.The bathrooms are good too,simple but with enough light and hot water.Desk people are very friendly,I can say it,there are three internet terminals,but not cheap.And a restaurant that looks uninspiring,but I never use it,can麓t talk about it,but there are endless options outside,althought by night many restaurants close earlyWell,and the better thing is the price,look into their website. 
